<p><b>Charlotte Maria Shaw Mason</b> (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1842-01-01"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="01-01"><a href="/wiki/January_1" title="January 1">January 1</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1842" title="1842">1842</a></span> – <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1923-01-16"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="01-16"><a href="/wiki/January_16" title="January 16">January 16</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1923" title="1923">1923</a></span>) was a <a href="/wiki/United_Kingdom" title="United Kingdom">British</a> educator who invested her life in improving the quality of children's education. Her ideas led to one of the primary methods of <a href="/wiki/Homeschooling" title="Homeschooling">homeschooling</a>.</p>
